According to https://eecs.berkeley.edu/resources/undergrads/cs/degree-reqs/enrollment-policy#lower, you do not have enrollment priority since you are technically a declared L&S major, even though it is CS. Because of this, the discussion section you are trying to enroll in may be open, but you must waitlist in it by default. Is the waitlist for the section in which you are trying to enroll full? If so, sign up for a different section with a waitlist that is not full. If the waitlist for the section that you selected is not full and you are still seeing this error, this could be a CalCentral issue and you should send an email to CS advising/sishelp.
--------------------------------------

I'd wager that you're trying to get into a full lab/discussion. That's not going to work. According to schedule planner, as of 9:14 PM PDT 7/28/17, "43 of 50 reserved seats filled for requirement: Computer Science BA with 3+ Terms in Attendance", so you should be able to get in. I did today.

According to https://eecs.berkeley.edu/resources/undergrads/cs/degree-reqs/enrollment-policy#lower, you do not have enrollment priority since you are technically a declared L&S major, even though it is CS. Because of this, the discussion section you are trying to enroll in may be open, but you must waitlist in it by default. Is the waitlist for the section in which you are trying to enroll full? If so, sign up for a different section with a waitlist that is not full. If the waitlist for the section that you selected is not full and you are still seeing this error, this could be a CalCentral issue and you should send an email to CS advising/sishelp.

As the student answer suggests, there are spots held for declared L&S CS majors; we've done that since the declaration process changed to precede taking 61C.  That won't allow a student to waitlist a section whose waitlist is full, however, regardless of class or major status.

I am trying to enroll in CS 61C for my phase 2 but I get the following error message when I try and enroll:

Error: Request not processed. There is no wait list available. The wait list request was not processed, as there are no wait list places available for one or more of the class sections in this request.

The section I am trying to enroll in says it is open and I declared the major this past semester, is there anything I am missing?
history.subject: Unable to enroll in CS 61C
